:\n\n1. **Trump said \"Ronaldo\" twice** in the transcript: \"I got to meet Ronaldo the other day\" and \"But Ronaldo is great\"\n2. **The remarks occurred at 11:13 a.m.** at the Kennedy Center\n3. **The transcript is explicitly titled** \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n4. **The formal draw was scheduled for 12 p.m.** with pre-draw coverage starting at 11:30 a.m.\n5. **The market asks** \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\"\n\nThe central question is whether remarks explicitly labeled as \"prior to\" and occurring before the scheduled draw time can reasonably be considered \"during\" the event. The market language and governing terms do not clearly include pre-event remarks, and the preponderance of evidence shows these remarks occurred before, not during, the draw.\n\nI will now submit my vote:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_92c8","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The preponderance of evidence shows Trump said 'Ronaldo' at 11:13 a.m. in remarks explicitly titled 'Prior to the FIFA World Cup Draw,' while the formal draw was scheduled for 12 p.m. ET. The market asks what Trump would say 'during' the draw, and the evidence indicates these remarks occurred before, not during, the event.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":141,"output":344,"cacheRead":54912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55397,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782769314114,"responseId":"gen-1782769314-GI9TOGmRjj7YWNpCYOx6"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_92c8","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex03a-20260629210937\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:3:C1\nremaining_ms: 711062\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex03a-202